   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Sixty-seven CHRIST BECAME A CURSE FOR US Scripture: Gal 3:13 The origin of the curse The curse came from sin.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>God brought in the curse after Adam sinned.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>God said, Cursed is the ground for thy sake Gen 3:17 .</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The sign of the curse The sign of the curse is thorns.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>After Adam sinned, the earth brought forth thorns because of the curse.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>So thorns are the sign of being cursed.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The outstanding feature of thorns is that they prick, causing pain.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The execution of the curse The curse is carried out through the law.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The law administers the curse.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Once man sinned, God s law then administered the curse upon man.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Therefore, the curse is related to the law of God, and is the demand of the righteousness of God upon sinners.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The nullification of the curse When Christ bore our sins, He also took our curse.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Since the problem of sin is resolved, so is the problem of the curse.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>When Christ bore our sins on the cross, He wore a crown of thorns.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Since the thorns are a sign of the curse, this shows that He took our curse on the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Since Christ was cursed in our stead on the cross, the demand of the law was fulfilled and He could redeem us from the curse of the law.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>How to have the curse removed</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
